name: 5 mins Shibuya Cat modern sunny  Shimokita
description:
Hi there, I am Wakana and I live with my two friendly cats.
I designed and built a house 11 years ago.
I am a business freelancer and one of my business is a real estate agent, so if you are looking for properties in Japan, I can be of a help!

My house is located near Ikenoue station, 5 minutes from Shibuya by Inokashira line. 12 mins walk to Shimokitazawa, hipster neighborhood.

If you have time, it would be nice to have a chat or go out for a drink.
neighborhood_overview:
The location is walkable distance to famous Shimokitazawa, known to be a posh residential area without any high rise buildings. In just 10 minutes you can be at the heart of the trendy, funky, and bohemian Shimokitazawa that has a smorgasbord of affordable yet mouth-wateringly good restaurants and vintage clothes shops. The house is well situated in between train stations: 5 minutes walk to Ikenoue station on Inokashira line, 3rd stop from Shibuya station. 8 minutes walk to Shimokitazawa station on Odakyu line, 10 minutes from Shimokitazawa to Shinjuku by train. All very convenient!

I am happy to share the map for the near-by restaurant (breakfast, lunch and dinner) once the booking is done!
host_about:
Hi there, I am Wakana! I am an openminded, friendly and postive person. That's what other say:)
I enjoy meeting new people via Airbnb and love it.

I used to live in Sydney and India altogether for 8 years in my 20s.

If you want to share some time with me, Let's grab drink or food!

name: Solar power/Car space/near to park
description:
It is a three floor house with car space. We are using the solar power in the house. Big living room and toilet in each floor. The house locates in a quiet and peaceful local residential area. 2 minutes walking to the local food market.
The nearest station is Musashi-Koyama station, 6 mins walking from our house. There is famous walking shopping street with a lot of restaurants, shops, cafes.
3 mins walking from the house, there is big pubic park.
We provide free car space for one car.
neighborhood_overview: Close to Big park, and the station. There are many traditional Japanese temples near by. And there is a real good nature Onsen close to us.
host_about:
Hello! My name is David, I have lived in Tokyo for more than 20 years. Before I came to Japan, I spent one year to study in Europe. So I can switch smoothly among Japanese, English and Chinese(Mandarin). 

I like travel and meet people. My wife, two lovely kids and I are living together, they are the most precious treasures for me. Even though we are foreigners, we keep tightly touch with local Japanese and community.

name: Easy to airport,Asakusa,Skytree,Ginza,Akihabara!
description:
Welcome to a vintage town called "Shitamachi area" in Tokyo!
You can feel like time slip to 1960's Tokyo (old but comfortable atmosphere).
Here is not a center of Tokyo though, there are a lot of nice local restaurants or food shops.
And easy access to center of Tokyo like ASAKUSA, SKYTREE, GINZA,UENO,AKIHABARA,TOKYO etc and Haneda/Narita airport.

I just renovated my house as modern Japanese style which is mixed with Western essence a bit.
7mins walk from Keisei Tateishi station.
* Not JR line
neighborhood_overview: Here is called "Shitamachi". We have many traditional Japanese culture and beautiful nature. You can see many real local Tokyo people,local popular restaurants and local warming heart! There is a nice river and park for relaxing.  There are also 100JPY shop or supermarket or Japanese sweets shop or beautiful river and park!
host_about: Hi,I am Kei. I am happy to get a chance to meet you ;) I am interested in travel,art and making new friends!

name: Shinjuku 3LDK House, 10min to Isetan
description:
Our house is only 7-min walking distance from the nearest station, Shinjuku-Sanchome Station, and 10-min walking distance from Shinjuku Center!

Newly decorated 3LDK, located in a quiet area of Shinjuku, 7-min walk to the Shinjuku-Sanchome Station where is on the Subway Fukutoshin Line, Toei Shinjuku Line and Marunouchi Line. 10-min walk to Shinjuku City Shopping Mall Isetan, 0101 and other department stores. The location is great and so convenient for you to travel anywhere in Tokyo.
neighborhood_overview:
Shinjuku is the center and transportation hub in Tokyo, known as major shopping area and nightlife. The central Shinjuku is in walking distance, but the house locates very quiet side near elementary school. It’s very safe and local.

- Maruetsu Supermarket (opens 24 hours) / 4-mins walk

- Daiso 100 Yen Shop/ 3-mins walk

- Family Mart Convenient Store / 3-mins walk

- Post Office Shinjuku Meijidori / 5 mins walk

- Artnia by Square Enix (Cafe) / 3-mins walk ** There are also many menus with motifs of popular games such as Dorakue and Final Fantasy with the goods section attached. **

No worries about eating and shopping, there are many restaurants and shopping malls nearby. Kabukicho nightlife area is in walking distance as well. The house location is very safe and quiet!
host_about:
Hello, my name is Kei！
I am from Tokyo. My wife is Chinese. 
We have a lovely daughter.

I love watching foreign dramas, eating ramen, meat and fish dishes.

I am really interested in foreign cultures. 
I am very excited to meet people from all around the world through Airbnb. 
My English is not very good, but I am practicing with my friend Jenny and I practice when I meet airbnb guests. I also learn a lot by reading the messages while communicating with guests.

 I am hosting guests in Japan from all over the world now. And I’m looking forward to travel the world using Airbnb.

I think people who choose to travel to Japan already have a certain interest for Japan, but my goal is to get everyone to love Japan more and more.

name: 120sqm 5LDK 3-Stories House 3BT JR Shin-Okubo 5min
description: A 5-minute walk to JR Yamanote Line Shin-Okubo Station, and a 5-minute walk to JR Chuo/Sobu Line Okubo Station. This newly renovated three-story detached house, 120 square meters in size, was refurbished in September 2024. The interior features both Western-style and traditional Japanese tatami bedrooms. There are a total of 5 bedrooms available for accommodation. The maximum bed arrangement includes 2 double beds, 2 single beds, 1 double sofa bed, and 3 sets of single Japanese futon mattresses.
neighborhood_overview:
Okubo area is a very lively area. In our neighborhood, there is supermarket, post office, traditional Japanese yakitori restaurant, 100-yen stores, drug stores, 24-hour open convenience store and so on. The area from Shin-Okubo station to Higashi-Shinjuku station is the famous Korean town. There are a lot of Korean cosmetic stores, restaurants and drug stores. You definitely won’t get bored and have no worries about finding restaurants. Central Shinjuku is just a tow away.

- 7-11, Family Mart Convenience Store / 2-mins walk

- My Basket and Olympic Supermarket / Opens 7AM-12AM, 3-mins walk

- Post office / 7 mins walk

- Cocokara Fine Okubo Station / Drug store 2 mins walk

- DonQuijote / 2 mins walk

name: 59㎡広々リビング駅近蔵前　浅草
description:
This room is characterized by a large kitchen and a spacious living room with two large sofas.There are 2 bedrooms, 1 Japanese-style room with 1 single bed and 2 futons on tatami mats.The Western-style room has a queen size bed and a semi-double bed.This entire rental unit is for guests only.I recently changed it to 2 bedrooms, so my review will be one bedroom.

The famous Asakusa Asakusa Temple is also a 15-minute walk, and this neighborhood is dotted with many shrines and temples.Inari-sama is also enshrined in front of the house.Kuramae is also famous as a city of monozukuri, and there are many leather goods shops and toy shops.There is a wholesaler of old-fashioned sweets and toys in the neighborhood.There are direct trains from both Narita Airport and Haneda Airport, and you can enjoy Ueno, Asakusa, Akihabara, Ryogoku, and Nihonbashi from here.

name: North Otsuka★ 602★Max4ppl★Airport50mins!
description:
Welcome to Otsuka station, which is Next to Ikebukuro Sta.
50mins from Nariata or Haneda airport!
2min walk to Otsuka sta.
Uniqlo,Starbucks and loft are in the building at the station.
★There are other same type rooms in the same building! Please contact me if you are more than 4 people. We can accommodate 24 people in total!
★You can drop your luggage before check in time ( please tell me in advance). You can drop it in the room after 11am.
Double bed x 2
Separated toilet and shower room
neighborhood_overview:
Otsuka station is in Toshima district in Tokyo and on the JR Yamanote line. This station has building for shopping!
Around Otsuka station, the atmosphere is like Showa era, which is rare compared with other towns in Tokyo.
It is because of old tram called Toden Arakawa line. It makes this town nice and old.
It would be fantastic to go to Japanese cake shop to get Daifuku.
You can enjoy shopping streets called SunMall Otsuka shopping streets. There are local products such as Japanese rice wine (sake), Shotyu ( also alcohol), rice, soy paste ( called Miso), another Japanese cake ( called Dorayaki). They are local brand " Otsuka Monogatari" and you can get them only in this shopping streets.
Also there are many restaurants and bars in this area.

Good location!!

neighborhood_overview:
About Ikebukuro
Ikebukuro is one of Tokyo's multiple city centers, found around the northwestern corner of the Yamanote Loop Line. This city offers plenty of entertainment, shopping and dining opportunities.
While not as large or well known as Akihabara, Ikebukuro is also a center of 'Otaku culture). Unlike Akihabara, Ikebukuro caters more to a female clientele with butler cafes and anime, manga and cosplay related shops such as Animate, Mandarake and K-nooks.

In Ikebukuro, there are;
・Sunshine City - a large shopping and entertainment complex which contains shops and restaurants, an aquarium, planetarium, museum, indoor theme parks. The focal point of the complex is the 240m high observation deck.

・Electronics Stores- Bic Camera and Yamada Denki. These two are the Japan's largest electronic retailers, clashing in this city.

・Department stores - Tobu and Seibu department stores on each sides of the station. They are one of the Japan's
host_about:
Hello. My name is Keisuke.
I am 26 years old, studied at Waseda University in Tokyo.
I spent my high school days in Australia and New Zealand.
When I think back the past, this was a life changing event for me. I stayed at some hosts' places and I had a warm welcome from them.
And I thought that time I would love to host travelers from all over the world. 

I, myself like to travel like you all do.
In (Phone number hidden by Airbnb) , I went to Hong Kong, Singapore, Taiwan and Thailand.
And last year, I visited France, Germany, Switzerland and Italy.
Hopefully I will visit other beautiful places this year.
I might stay with some of you when I go visit your place :)

I'm not a perfect host but I'm trying to be perfect!
Any kind of feedback is really appreciated.
Let me make your trip a wonderful one.

Hope you have a wonderful time here!
Thank you,
Keisuke

name: Asakusa_Best Location/Max10p/2mins to Sensoji_K18
description:
My house is located central of Asakusa and renovated on Summer of 2019.

Awesome location! Only 5 minutes walk from Asakusa station.
You can feel real JAPAN!
My house is up to 11 people, good for family and friends! There are 2 bath and 2 toilets.

〇Great location
Walking
3 mins to Sensoji(Asakusa kannnon temple)
4 mins to Nakamise Street(oldest shopping street)
5 mins to Asakusa station

Train
5 mins to Ueno & Ameyoko Street
13 min to Akihabara
25 min to Shinjuku

Hi-Speed WIFI is available.
host_about:
Hi my friends,

My name is Kei.

Thank you for visiting my account!

Let me introduce myself first, 

I used to work in financial field and often went on a business trip in the U.S and some big cities in Asia.
My business went pretty well, but it was such an intensive work. I was always under huge pressure, especially during the business trip. So, on my business trip, I mostly preferred staying at Airbnb than hotels as I could put myself in relaxing and comfortable situation that I felt like I was at home. 

Through my Airbnb experience, I got a glimpse of new other culture while talking to the owner of the Airbnb and other guests. This experience was unforgettable for me, and I got interested in communication with people in other culture.

Recently, I’ve settled down my life here in Tokyo, then, decided to be an Airbnb host to welcome people from all over the world. 

In order for you to feel “Real Japan Life”, I carefully chose furniture and household items in my apartment. 

Hope you will like my apartment and have a great time in Tokyo!

Thank you.

name: Quiet residential Shinjuku area,8 min on foot Sta
description:
We have prepared the room to welcome new travelers in a quiet residential area.
It is an 8-minute walk from Takadanobaba Station and a 5-minute train ride to Shinjuku Ikebukuro.
There are convenience stores, supermarkets, countless taverns, ramen shops, and cafes nearby.
I also like to travel, so I always try to welcome you from the standpoint of Guest.
We look forward to welcoming you!
neighborhood_overview:
About Takadanobaba
There are tons of restaurants and shops within a 10-minute walk, and it is famous as a student district including Waseda University. The Kanda River flows nearby and it is a lively and safe area that is easy to spend.

About Shinjuku
Shinjuku is one of the biggest cities in Tokyo. Great spot for shopping, sightseeing, drinking, night life and etc. Moreover, Shinjuku is the most popular area for tourists. Shinjuku is the best location to stay for a Tokyo trip with easy access to any area in Tokyo. Trains like JR lines and Tokyo METRO subway lines will take you literally anywhere.

In Shinjuku, there are;
･Kabuki-Cho – any kind of night life you can enjoy
･Shinjuku National Gyoen Park – Japanese traditonal style garden
･Isetan Department Store – shopping mall with luxury and latest fashion brand stores.
･Tokyo Metropolitan Government Office - Free observation deck at 202m high. You can see Mt.Fuji on sunny days.

host_about:
Hello, my name is Kei！
I am from Tokyo. My wife is Chinese. 
We have a lovely daughter.

I love watching foreign dramas, eating ramen, meat and fish dishes.

I am really interested in foreign cultures. 
I am very excited to meet people from all around the world through Airbnb. 
My English is not very good, but I am practicing with my friend Jenny and I practice when I meet airbnb guests. I also learn a lot by reading the messages while communicating with guests.

 I am hosting guests in Japan from all over the world now. And I’m looking forward to travel the world using Airbnb.

I think people who choose to travel to Japan already have a certain interest for Japan, but my goal is to get everyone to love Japan more and more.

neighborhood_overview:
About Ikebukuro
Ikebukuro is one of Tokyo's multiple city centers, found around the northwestern corner of the Yamanote Loop Line. This city offers plenty of entertainment, shopping and dining opportunities.
While not as large or well known as Akihabara, Ikebukuro is also a center of 'Otaku culture). Unlike Akihabara, Ikebukuro caters more to a female clientele with butler cafes and anime, manga and cosplay related shops such as Animate, Mandarake and K-nooks.

In Ikebukuro, there are;
・Sunshine City - a large shopping and entertainment complex which contains shops and restaurants, an aquarium, planetarium, museum, indoor theme parks. The focal point of the complex is the 240m high observation deck.

・Electronics Stores- Bic Camera and Yamada Denki. These two are the Japan's largest electronic retailers, clashing in this city.

・Department stores - Tobu and Seibu department stores on each sides of the station. They are one of the Japan's
host_about:
Hello. My name is Keisuke.
I am 26 years old, studied at Waseda University in Tokyo.
I spent my high school days in Australia and New Zealand.
When I think back the past, this was a life changing event for me. I stayed at some hosts' places and I had a warm welcome from them.
And I thought that time I would love to host travelers from all over the world. 

I, myself like to travel like you all do.
In (Phone number hidden by Airbnb) , I went to Hong Kong, Singapore, Taiwan and Thailand.
And last year, I visited France, Germany, Switzerland and Italy.
Hopefully I will visit other beautiful places this year.
I might stay with some of you when I go visit your place :)

I'm not a perfect host but I'm trying to be perfect!
Any kind of feedback is really appreciated.
Let me make your trip a wonderful one.

Hope you have a wonderful time here!
Thank you,
Keisuke

neighborhood_overview:
About Shibuya
Shibuya is one of the biggest spot to go shopping, sightseeing, and night pleasure etc. and actually, Shibuya is the most popular area for travelers. Also it is the best place to access any area in Tokyo easily by using JR Line, and subway (called METRO).


Access list
(a trains map and a guide book are prepared)
・Akihabara - 27mins, using Yamanote Line(JR)
・Tokyo - 23mins, using Yamanote Line(JR)
・Shinjuku – 6mins, using Saikyo Line(JR)
・Harajuku – 3mins, using Yamanote Line(JR)
・Ginza – 15mins, using Ginza Line(METRO)
・Tokyo sky tree(Oshiage) – 33mins, using Hanzomon Line(METRO)
・Roppongi – 13mins, using Yamanote Line(JR) and Hibiya Line(METRO)


In Shibuya, there are;
・Shibuya Times Square - in front of the station
・Dogenzaka – night pleasure spot
・Ceruleantower - nice restaurants on 40F
・Hikarie – shopping mall
・109 - cloth shop for boys and girls

-----
host_about:
Hello. My name is Keisuke.
I am 26 years old, studied at Waseda University in Tokyo.
I spent my high school days in Australia and New Zealand.
When I think back the past, this was a life changing event for me. I stayed at some hosts' places and I had a warm welcome from them.
And I thought that time I would love to host travelers from all over the world. 

I, myself like to travel like you all do.
In (Phone number hidden by Airbnb) , I went to Hong Kong, Singapore, Taiwan and Thailand.
And last year, I visited France, Germany, Switzerland and Italy.
Hopefully I will visit other beautiful places this year.
I might stay with some of you when I go visit your place :)

I'm not a perfect host but I'm trying to be perfect!
Any kind of feedback is really appreciated.
Let me make your trip a wonderful one.

Hope you have a wonderful time here!
Thank you,
Keisuke

neighborhood_overview:
About Takadanobaba
There are tons of restaurants and shops within a 10-minute walk, and it is famous as a student district including Waseda University. The Kanda River flows nearby and it is a lively and safe area that is easy to spend.

About Shinjuku
Shinjuku is one of the biggest cities in Tokyo. Great spot for shopping, sightseeing, drinking, night life and etc. Moreover, Shinjuku is the most popular area for tourists. Shinjuku is the best location to stay for a Tokyo trip with easy access to any area in Tokyo. Trains like JR lines and Tokyo METRO subway lines will take you literally anywhere.

In Shinjuku, there are;
･Kabuki-Cho – any kind of night life you can enjoy
･Shinjuku National Gyoen Park – Japanese traditonal style garden
･Isetan Department Store – shopping mall with luxury and latest fashion brand stores.
･Tokyo Metropolitan Government Office - Free observation deck at 202m high. You can see Mt.Fuji on sunny days.

description:
5 mins walk to JR Yamanote Line Shin-Okubo Sta. and JR Chuo/Sobu Line Okubo Sta. Newly renovated three-story detached house, featuring both Western and Japanese-style tatami bedrooms. 3 bedrooms with 3 double beds, 1 double sofa bed, and 2 sets of single Japanese futon mattresses.

Located in the heart of the city, the house offers convenient transportation and a quiet, safe environment. Convenience stores, supermarkets, restaurants, and the lively Shinjuku area are all within walking distance.
host_about:
Hello, my name is Kei！
I am from Tokyo. My wife is Chinese. 
We have a lovely daughter.

I love watching foreign dramas, eating ramen, meat and fish dishes.

I am really interested in foreign cultures. 
I am very excited to meet people from all around the world through Airbnb. 
My English is not very good, but I am practicing with my friend Jenny and I practice when I meet airbnb guests. I also learn a lot by reading the messages while communicating with guests.

 I am hosting guests in Japan from all over the world now. And I’m looking forward to travel the world using Airbnb.

I think people who choose to travel to Japan already have a certain interest for Japan, but my goal is to get everyone to love Japan more and more.

Welcome to Asakusabashi/Akihabara!

It's the ideal Tokyo sightseeing area.

Situated on the 3rd floor with elevator access.

Spacious 76 m² 3-bedroom 2LDK apartment.

name: 2stops2Ueno 1room  max3pax 5mins from station 202
description:
Welcome to Kei's APT in Kaminagazato Kita-ku, Tokyo, Japan.

Located in a quiet and traditional neighborhood with easy access transportations.

Transportation Access (From JR KamiNakazato Station):

10 minutes to Ueno (direct, no transit)

13 minutes to Akihabara (direct, no transit)

17 minutes to Tokyo Station (direct, no transit)

25 minutes to Asakusa (1 transit)

20 minutes to Ikebukuro (1 transit)

25 minutes to Shinjuku (1 transit)

35 minutes to Shibuya (1 transit)
neighborhood_overview:
Tokyo's Kita Ward, Kami-Nakazato, is a neighborhood where historical charm and modern vibes seamlessly blend. Located in Kita Ward, Tokyo, it is close to the Arakawa River, offering beautiful natural surroundings with abundant green spaces and riverside scenery, making it an ideal spot for residents to relax and unwind. Kami-Nakazato is renowned for its tranquil living environment, featuring numerous residential areas with comprehensive amenities and convenient transportation. The JR Keihin-Tohoku Line's Kami-Nakazato Station is just a short walk away, providing easy access to central Tokyo and other major areas.

Additionally, Kami-Nakazato retains a touch of traditional culture, with historic temples and shrines nearby. The famous Asukayama Park, a popular cherry blossom viewing spot, is also in the vicinity, along with museums and libraries, adding to the area's cultural richness. The neighborhood is dotted with restaurants and shops, catering to daily needs. Kami-Nakazato
host_about:
Hi my friends,

My name is Kei.

Thank you for visiting my account!

Let me introduce myself first, 

I used to work in financial field and often went on a business trip in the U.S and some big cities in Asia.
My business went pretty well, but it was such an intensive work. I was always under huge pressure, especially during the business trip. So, on my business trip, I mostly preferred staying at Airbnb than hotels as I could put myself in relaxing and comfortable situation that I felt like I was at home. 

Through my Airbnb experience, I got a glimpse of new other culture while talking to the owner of the Airbnb and other guests. This experience was unforgettable for me, and I got interested in communication with people in other culture.

Recently, I’ve settled down my life here in Tokyo, then, decided to be an Airbnb host to welcome people from all over the world. 

In order for you to feel “Real Japan Life”, I carefully chose furniture and household items in my apartment. 

Hope you will like my apartment and have a great time in Tokyo!

Thank you.

name: スカイツリービュー/家族向けの3ベッドルームアパートメント/押上駅から徒歩7分
description:
A floating resort vacation stay in the heart of the city.

It is a prime location with a view of Tokyo Skytree in front of you, but once you step into the room, you'll have a bright and sunny Asian resort-like space that doesn't make you feel the hustle and bustle of the city.

Most of the furniture, dishes, and decorations are made by locals from Asian resorts such as Indonesia.We will give you a comfortable time to feel the power of nature, such as the sound of the blue sea and the waves, the sound of birds, the colors and scents of flowers, and the scent of the sun.

There is a living area for everyone to hang out in and three bedrooms with privacy.
Each bedroom is designed with a different concept, so choose which one you like.

Access to famous tourist destinations such as Akihabara, Shinjuku, Shibuya, and Ginza is also easy, and direct trains to Narita Airport are also available.
